description: This file defines a data model for movie scripts using Pydantic, and sets up two Agent instances for generating movie scripts via different modes (JSON and structured output). It also includes example method calls to print responses for a given prompt.

classes.name: MovieScript
classes.description: A Pydantic model representing the structure of a movie script, including setting, ending, genre, name, characters, and storyline.

methods.name: print_response
methods.description: Method of Agent class used to print the response for a given prompt.
